HEADWORD: Semibreve
<hw>Sem"i*breve`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>semi-</ets> + <ets>breve</ets>: cf. F. <ets>semi-breve</ets>, It.
<ets>semibreve</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Formerly written
<asp>semibref</asp>.]</altsp> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A note of half the
time or duration of the breve; -- now usually called a <xex>whole
note</xex>. It is the longest note in general use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

